theorem Topology.closure_union_interior_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure A ∪ interior A = closure A := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `closure A` is contained in the union by definition, and
    -- `interior A` is trivially contained in the union.
    intro x hx
    exact Or.inl hx
  · -- The union is contained in `closure A` because `interior A ⊆ closure A`.
    intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hCl => exact hCl
    | inr hInt =>
        have : x ∈ closure A :=
          (Topology.interior_subset_closure (A := A)) hInt
        exact this

theorem Topology.interior_inter_open_left
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    interior (A ∩ B) = A ∩ interior B := by
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately and finish with `Set.Subset.antisymm`.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    -- `x` lies in `A ∩ B`.
    have hAB : x ∈ A ∩ B := interior_subset hx
    have hxA : x ∈ A := hAB.1
    -- Since `A ∩ B ⊆ B`, `x` is also in `interior B`.
    have hxIntB : x ∈ interior B := by
      have hsub : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B := by
        intro y hy
        exact hy.2
      exact (interior_mono hsub) hx
    exact And.intro hxA hxIntB
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxA, hxIntB⟩
    -- The set `A ∩ interior B` is open.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A ∩ interior B) := hA.inter isOpen_interior
    -- It is contained in `A ∩ B`.
    have hsub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      have hyA : y ∈ A := hy.1
      have hyB : y ∈ B := interior_subset hy.2
      exact And.intro hyA hyB
    -- Therefore, using `interior_maximal`, it is contained in the interior of `A ∩ B`.
    have hxInt : x ∈ interior (A ∩ B) :=
      (interior_maximal hsub hOpen) ⟨hxA, hxIntB⟩
    exact hxInt

theorem Topology.interior_inter_open_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} (hB : IsOpen B) :
    interior (A ∩ B) = interior A ∩ B := by
  -- As before, prove both inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    -- `x` lies in `A ∩ B`.
    have hAB : x ∈ A ∩ B := interior_subset hx
    have hxB : x ∈ B := hAB.2
    -- Since `A ∩ B ⊆ A`, `x` is also in `interior A`.
    have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A := by
      have hsub : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
        intro y hy; exact hy.1
      exact (interior_mono hsub) hx
    exact And.intro hxIntA hxB
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxIntA, hxB⟩
    -- The set `interior A ∩ B` is open.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (interior A ∩ B) := isOpen_interior.inter hB
    -- It is contained in `A ∩ B`.
    have hsub : (interior A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      have hyA : y ∈ A := interior_subset hy.1
      exact And.intro hyA hy.2
    -- Conclude that `x` is in the interior of `A ∩ B`.
    have hxInt : x ∈ interior (A ∩ B) :=
      (interior_maximal hsub hOpen) ⟨hxIntA, hxB⟩
    exact hxInt

theorem Topology.isOpen_iff_interior_closure_eq_of_isClosed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsClosed A) :
    IsOpen A ↔ interior (closure A) = (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hOpen
    simpa using
      Topology.interior_closure_eq_of_isClosed_of_isOpen
        (A := A) hA hOpen
  · intro hEq
    have : IsOpen (interior (closure A)) := isOpen_interior
    simpa [hEq] using this

theorem Topology.interior_eq_empty_of_interior_closure_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : interior (closure A) = (∅ : Set X)) :
    interior A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  -- `interior A` is always contained in `interior (closure A)`.
  have hsubset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
    Topology.interior_subset_interior_closure (A := A)
  -- Rewrite with the assumption `h` to obtain the desired inclusion.
  have hsubset' : interior A ⊆ (∅ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h] using hsubset
  -- The reverse inclusion `∅ ⊆ interior A` is automatic.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm hsubset' (Set.empty_subset _)
